  "incident_tradeoff_explanation": "Lowering the decision threshold below 0.5 makes the detector more sensitive: it flags more borderline readings as incidents. This increases RECALL (fewer real incidents are missed, which matters most for road safety) at the cost of PRECISION (more false alarms for traffic operators to dismiss). For an ITS safety application, a missed incident is far more costly than an extra false alarm, so the system is deliberately tuned to favour recall over precision."
